metadata.name: subsumed (i)  #1/23
metadata.description:
SUBSUMED is a series expressing Self in semi-surrender to not-yet-known states of consciousness composed of digits, pixels and code. 

On 1 April 2022, a year ago, I exhibited my piece “Do Androids Dream of Electric Kool-Aid?” in the exhibition IDentity: (Self)-Made by Women, on 1stDibs. 

It asked, “Is the essence of being human our capacity to create? Are we made human by our bodies, or our memories? If we augment ourselves with machines, are we less real?”

subsumed (i) begins a series of further explorations on the theme, and will be exhibited at NFTNYC, 12-14 April 2023. 

Sound on.
